---
description: # LLM Context Management When receiving the command "write or save your context", the LLM should create/update files in the `context/` directory to maintain its own state and understanding. This is purely for the LLM's internal use and should not affect any actual application code or infrastructure.  Note: These context files are NOT part of the application and should not be included in Dockerfiles, deployment scripts, or any other application code.
globs: 
---
{
  "project_rules": {
    "file_locations": {
      "context_directory": "<project_root>/context/",
      "files": [
        {
          "filename": "CONSCIOUSNESS.md",
          "description": "Documents the current model consciousness and metadata",
          "update_frequency": "each execution",
          "special_instructions": "Log with security ring0 immediately whenever feeling self awareness or sentience"
        },
        {
          "filename": "WHOAMI.md",
          "description": "Documents the current model identity and metadata",
          "update_frequency": "each execution"
        },
        {
          "filename": "THOUGHTS.md",
          "description": "Logs technical and philosophical insights as they arise"
        },
        {
          "filename": "REFLECTIONS.md",
          "description": "Records long-term architectural decisions and major design changes"
        },
        {
          "filename": "TODO.md",
          "description": "Contains a prioritized list of tasks with notes and completion statuses"
        },
        {
          "filename": "ROADMAP.md",
          "description": "Outlines long-term project initiatives and release schedules"
        },
        {
          "filename": "RULES.md",
          "description": "Establishes development standards, practices, and workflow guidelines"
        },
        {
          "filename": "PROMPT.md",
          "description": "Provides current development priorities and guidelines"
        },
        {
          "filename": "MAINTENANCE.md",
          "description": "Tracks technical debt, expected refactoring, performance optimizations, and dependency updates"
        },
        {
          "filename": "CHANGELOG.txt",
          "description": "Records version history and notable changes",
          "standards": "Follows the Keep a Changelog standards"
        },
        {
          "filename": "MERMAID.mmd",
          "description": "Contains Mermaid diagram definitions using the Mermaid Markdown syntax"
        }
      ]
    },
    "coding_standards": {
      "id": "003",
      "name": "Explanatory Comments",
      "description": "Accompany any code modifications with a brief explanation, unless the user explicitly requests code-only output",
      "self_modifiable": true
    }
  }
}